comment: RATR shows that Adams (OKC) firms up as he sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Matthews (DAL) grabs and holds Durant (OKC) affecting his FOM away from the ball.
Matthews (DAL) and Durant (OKC) engage and separate away from the ball.
Felton (DAL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Westbrook (OKC), who loses the ball OOB.
Mejri (DAL) firms up as he sets the screen on Waiters (OKC) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] Westbrook (OKC) moves his pivot foot.
[Incidental or immaterial] Durant (OKC) moves his pivot foot after catching the entry pass.
[Incidental or immaterial] Harris (DAL) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Matthews (DAL) and Durant (OKC) briefly engage and separate away from the ball.
Adams (OKC) firms up as he sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ibaka (OKC) sets the screen on Felton (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
LATR shows Mejri (DAL) has his arm over Adams' (OKC) shoulder, affecting his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Adams (OKC) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Felton's (DAL) drive to the basket and shot attempt. Felton initiates contact on the play.
Mejri (DAL) is the last player to touch the ball prior to it going OOB.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that possession be awarded to OKC was upheld.
Ibaka (OKC) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Adams (OKC) sets the screen on Matthews (DAL) without giving him room to avoid the contact.
Matthews (DAL) cleanly strips the ball from Durant (OKC).
Adams (OKC) commits a take foul on Felton (DAL).
Harris (DAL) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
[Incidental or immaterial] Waiters (OKC) grabs Anderson's (DAL) jersey on the inbound pass.
Westbrook (OKC) makes contact with Felton (DAL), affecting his ability to catch the pass.
Waiters (OKC) clamps Matthews' (DAL) arm and pulls him to the floor.
Nowitzki (DAL) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Durant's (OKC) driving layup attempt.
Anderson (DAL) makes incidental contact with Durant’s (OKC) off arm/shoulder while he is attempting his shot. The contact does not affect Durant’s follow-through.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Adams (OKC) released the ball prior to the game clock expiring was overturned.
